"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-05-Olympic-sailing-venues-Marseille-Marina-and-Qingdao-Sailing-Center-1vONOSsEGfS-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  A view of the boathouses and slipways at the Marseille Marina in France on April 2, 2024\\u00c2\\u00a0/IC  Athletes train at the Marseille Marina for the Paris Olympics on July 25, 2024 in Marseille, France. /IC  The Mediterranean climate of Marseille offers mild winters and hot summers, with consistent wind conditions that are ideal for sailing. The sailing events for the Paris Olympics are taking place at Marseille Marina, one of the oldest ports in the Mediterranean. It has been a central hub of maritime activity and trade for centuries. Located in the south of France, the port is surrounded by a rich tapestry of cultural landmarks, including the Fort Saint-Jean, providing a stunning backdrop for the Olympic sailing events.  A view of the Qingdao International Sailing Center in Shandong Province on June 28, 2024 /CFP  A night view of the Qingdao International Sailing Center in Shandong Province on June 28, 2024 /CFP  In contrast, the Qingdao International Sailing Center, located on the east coast of China in Qingdao, Shandong Province, represents modernity and innovation. Constructed specifically for the 2008 Beijing Olympics, the center boasts state-of-the-art facilities and infrastructure designed to meet international sailing standards. The city of Qingdao, known as the \\\"Sailing Capital of China,\\\" also has a strong maritime history and vibrant sailing community.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"